<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,1443,1755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
This species has been misidentified throughout the Caribbean as either 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1767)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasilianorum">
<emphasis box="[1098,1304,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">X. brasilianorum</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1767)
</taxonomicName>
or, less frequently, as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1793)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[527,843,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis box="[527,629,1540,1563]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">X. morio</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, J. C." box="[643,833,1539,1563]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref12670" refString="Fabricius, J. C. 1793. Entomologia systematica emendata et aucta. Secundum classes, ordines, genera, species adjectis synonimis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. Proft; Copenhagen. vol. 2, viii + 519 p." type="book" year="1793">Fabricius, 1793</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Both misidentifications refer to Brazilian species not present in the West Indies (
<bibRefCitation author="Hurd" box="[574,710,1571,1595]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref13527" refString="Hurd Jr., P. D. 1978. An annotated catalog of the carpenter bees Xylocopa Latreille of the Western Hemisphere (Anthophoridae). Smithsonian Institution Press; Washington. 106 p." type="book" year="1978">Hurd 1978</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S." box="[728,892,1571,1595]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="71 - 74" refId="ref14790" refString="Moure, J. S. 2003. Uma especie nova de Xylocopa Latreille, 1802, e notas sobre Xylocopa transitoria Perez e X. mordax Smith (Hymenoptera, Apoidea). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia 47: 71 - 74." type="journal article" year="2003">Moure (2003)</bibRefCitation>
provided taxonomic notes on 
<emphasis box="[1252,1387,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName box="[1252,1383,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mordax">X. mordax</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The common name of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[589,733,1603,1627]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
is “cigarrón” (large cigar). 
<bibRefCitation author="Martorell" box="[1066,1269,1603,1627]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref14454" refString="Martorell L. F. 1976. Annotated food plant catalog of the insects of Puerto Rico. Agricultural Experiment Station, University of Puerto Rico. 303 p." type="book" year="1976">Martorell (1976)</bibRefCitation>
and O’Farril- 
<collectingCountry box="[192,276,1635,1659]" name="Saint Kitts and Nevis" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Nieves</collectingCountry>
and Medina-Gaud (2007) mention that this species drills into dry branches and tree trunks. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, G. C. &amp; R. O. Woodbury" box="[192,553,1667,1691]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="639 - 660" refId="ref13760" refString="Jackson, G. C., and R. O. Woodbury. 1976. Host plants of the carpenter bee, Xylocopa brasilianorum (L.), in Puerto Rico. Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico 60: 639 - 660." type="journal article" year="1976">Jackson and Woodbury (1976)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Jackson, G. C." box="[610,790,1667,1691]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="255 - 265" refId="ref13713" refString="Jackson, G. C. 1986. Additional host plants of the carpenter bee, Xylocopa brasilianorum (L.) (Hymenoptera: Apoidea), in Puerto Rico. Journal of Agriculture of the University of Puerto Rico 70: 255 - 265." type="journal article" year="1986">Jackson (1986)</bibRefCitation>
studied the nectar and pollen-gathering activities and nesting sites of 
<taxonomicName box="[377,502,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mordax">
<emphasis box="[377,502,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">X. mordax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivera-Marchand, B. &amp; J. D. Ackerman" box="[515,995,1699,1723]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="635 - 642" refId="ref15439" refString="Rivera-Marchand, B. and J. D. Ackerman. 2006. Bat pollination breakdown in the Caribbean columnar cactus Pilosocereus royenii. Biotropica 38: 635 - 642." type="journal article" year="2006">Rivera-Marchand and Ackerman (2006)</bibRefCitation>
determined that this species was the only effective pollinator of the cactus 
<taxonomicName box="[643,883,1731,1755]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Pilosocereus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="royenii">
<emphasis box="[643,883,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Pilosocereus royenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Byles and Rowley.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
